<paragraph id="8B8436B79556FFB1CFF75C56FE7E26D2" blockId="63.[151,1437,1482,2013]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">
<emphasis id="B94FEAA59556FFB1CFF75C56FEA2261A" bold="true" box="[151,347,1627,1653]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Local synonymy</emphasis>
: The synonymy for this species in South African waters is long and convoluted, and most of the “black-tipped” sharks are of other 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B4D349556FFB1CD335C72FD1426F6" authorityName="Blainville" authorityYear="1816" box="[595,749,1663,1689]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Carcharhinidae" genus="Carcharhinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carcharhiniformes" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B94FEAA59556FFB1CD335C72FD1426F6" box="[595,749,1663,1689]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Carcharhinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species. A discussion of the issue is presented below in the Remarks section.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
